s of ingredients like sand, water, rock, silver, etc. Generally there are two types of concrete plants used for mixing concrete. The first one is Ready Mix plant and second is Central Mix batch plant. In ready mix plants, all ingredients are mixed with each other except water. Water is added to it when it is used for construction at the construction site. On the other hand, central mix batch plant includes all ingredients with water and is used when construction is going to be started.\r\n\r\nThe center of any concrete batching plant is the mixer. There are three types of mixers: tilt, pan, and twin shaft mixer. The twin shaft mixer ensures even mixture of concrete and large output, whereas the tilt mixer offers a consistent mix with much less maintenance, labor and cost.\r\nConcrete batch plants are mostly used by construction companies where they produce a large amount of concrete. They are quite expensive and a company cannot afford more than one plant. If a company is going to increase its concrete batch plant then they have to increase their labor, transportation cost and many more costs.\r\n\r\nTYPES OF CONCRETE BATCH PLANTS Concrete batch plants fall into two broad categories. One is a permanent high capacity batching plant which is normally constituted of silos, bins, concrete batchers, conveyors, and control equipments. Listed below are three types of permanent high capacity batching plants.\r\n\r\n•    Robo-mix plants: This is the most popular form of concrete batch plants and consists of a drum mixer. It is the most ideal to use it on construction site.\r\n•    Hydro-mix plants: This is the second most popular type of concrete batch plant and consists of a conveyor belt discharge system. It is used with conventional truck mixers.\r\n•    Bin-Fed Batching Plant: This plant is fully automatic and has its own hydraulic off-loading legs.\r\n\r\nThe other type of concrete batching plants which are rapidly gaining popularity and can be seen widely used in construction sites, is called the Mobile (or Portable) batching plant. The mobile batching units include the structure which carries the batchers, conveyors, scales, control equipment and small silos to be used at the construction site. They provide a lot of cost and time savings and increase efficiency at the building site. Many a construction headache has been solved using this relatively cheaper alternative. facility which allows construction site managers to reduce cost but maintain quality.\r\n\r\nWith the advent of technology, most modern concrete batch plants use computer aided control to assist in the quick and accurate measurement of ingredients, as well as coordinate the functioning of various parts and accessories for safe operation. Since the quality and performance of concrete is highly dependent on the water content, these sophisticated systems will use moisture probes to gauge the amount of water that is part of the aggregate (sand and rock) material during weighing.  If there is a need for changing the water content, it will automatically do so.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Concrete Batch Plants','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-6','','','2011-05-18 16:13:27','2011-05-18 16:13:27','',2,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/2-revision-6',0,'revision','',0),(45,1,'2011-05-16 16:16:00','2011-05-16 16:16:00','<a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/FHA1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-15\" title=\"FHA\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/FHA1.jpg\" alt=\"FHA logo\" width=\"100\" height=\"97\" /></a>The Federal Highway Administration will hold three online informational meetings next week about plans for Interstate 3.\r\n\r\nThe FHA is working on a \"Conceptual Feasibility Report\" to identify potential alignments that connect designated urban areas, develop cost estimates for various design levels, and recommend implementation steps. Interstate 3 may 