y used when it comes to using ready-mixed  concrete. This is because it saves a lot of time and is ideal with large  projects. It originated from the 1940s, when the world was trying to  build back after the war, and is still popular in many building projects  now. The batch plant mixer is perfect to be used in small spaces and for larger commercial projects. R&amp;S Industries manufacturers precision engineered Central Tilt  Batch Plant Mixers are manufactured in capacities of 10, 12, 15, and 18 cubic yards.\r\n<h1>Why use a batch plant mixer?</h1>\r\nBy using a batch plant mixer, the means that the concrete will then  need to be moved to a truck mixer to be able to deliver the product to the job site.\r\n<h2>Various Types - Batch plant mixer</h2>\r\n•    Ready-mix concrete can be mixed in a variety of ways. Concrete  can be mixed with the truck mixers, and this type of concrete is called  truck-mixed, or transit-mixed, concrete.  Ready-mix concrete can also be  mixed in a plant mixer, then moved to the drum of the truck mixer.  These central mixing plants use a stationary mixer to partially mix the  concrete. This type of concrete is called shrink-mixed concrete, since  it reduces the volume of the concrete. The final type of concrete mixing  used is called central mixing, or wet batch, concrete. Central mixing  is cost-effective since it requires less wear on the truck drums.  However, some plant mixers may require more maintenance, but they  produce higher quality concrete due to the superior mixing.\r\n<h3>Function of batch plant mixer</h3>\r\n•    Ready-mix concrete is usually delivered by trucks with rotating  drum mixers. Drum mixer trucks are designed with a pair of blades that  spin one way to mix the concrete, and then can spin the opposite  direction to release the mixture. Although most concrete mixer trucks  discharge concrete from the back, newer trucks feature front-discharge  chutes. These front-discharge trucks require less maneuvering to place  the concrete in the correct location.\r\n<h3>Types of batch plant mixer</h3>\r\n•    Types of plant mixers include: tilt drum mixer, horizontal shaft  mixers, pan mixers and slurry mixers. Tilt drum mixers are the most  common and are known for their efficiency. Horizontal shaft mixers are  good for producing higher-quality concrete products because of their  powerful blending capabilities.  Pan mixers are used for pre-cast concrete operations.\r\n<h3>Benefits to using a batch plant mixer</h3>\r\n•    For smaller projects, the newer \"mix mobiles\" are popular. These  volumetric mixers, or mobile concrete plants on wheels, offer freshly  mixed concrete on demand. Contractors put in sand, coarse aggregate,  cement, water and other additives to the belts and bins to create fresh  concrete on-site. For smaller projects, customers can order more exact  amounts when using the volumetric mixers. Often when using drum mixers,  they must order extra concrete to ensure that they have enough for the  project. Contractors also save money because this method produces less  waste. Some contractors also buy specialized pumps for pumping ready-mix  concrete. If customers need a concrete pumped in, contractors who own  their own pumps are at a significant advantage. Contractors can also  contract out their pumping services to other concrete companies without a  pump.\r\n<h2>Considerations</h2>\r\n•    For concrete equipment, preventative care is essential for good  use. It is necessary to pressure wash, check and adjust the equipment as  needed. Some contractors may buy used equipment because the costs of  mixers, pumps and other equipment is quite high. However, a breakdown in  equipment may irritate customers and cause a contractor to lose a  valuable contract. New equipment may be worth the cost for its  reliability factor and manufacturer\'s warranty.\r\n\r\n<strong>Related Articles:</strong>\r\n\r\n<address>For more information on purchasing <a href=\"../../\" target=\"_blank\">concrete batch plants </a>\r\n</address> <address>More information on <a title=\"portable concrete plants\" href=\"../portable-concrete-plants\">portable concrete plants</a></address> <address>More information on <a href=\"http://http//www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/mobile-batch-plant\">mobile match plant</a></address> <address>More information on <a title=\"batch plant mixers\" href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com\">batch plant mixer</a></address>&nbsp;','Batch Plant Mixer','','publish','open','open','','batch-plant-mixer','','','2011-06-13 20:18:23','2011-06-13 20:18:23','',0,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/?p=46',0,'post','',0),(47,1,'2011-05-16 21:30:36','2011-05-16 21:30:36','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','46-revision','','','2011-05-16 21:30:36','2011-05-16 21:30:36','',46,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/46-revision',0,'revision','',0),(276,1,'2011-06-27 17:15:16','2011-06-27 17:15:16','What is a Recycle Crusher? When renovations take place or when structures which have been made  of concrete are entirely demolished, they create rubble which needs to  be recycled. Concrete or crusher recycling is the name given to the  recycling of rubble created by such demolition. Before this  method of recycling was available, concrete waste was deposited as landfills but the  advantages of concrete crusher recycling has made it a better option especially  since now various environmental laws have been set up against dumping of  waste. Crusher recycling also keeps the costs of construction low.\r\n<h1>By-product of a Recycle Crusher</h1>\r\nRecycling of concrete leads to the production of industrial by-products  which include fly ash, slag and silica fume. Apart from these by-products, waste  materials are a raw material for several other products including cement and  tires etc. Cement makes use of silica, calcium, alumina and iron which  are the recycled by-product of sand from steel casting and fly ash from  power stations. Kiln waste is dust that is produced in the production of  cement and despite it being a dust; it is still recycled back as a raw  material into kiln. Even concrete which has become very old has a use;  it can be used as a granular fill for road beds after being recycled.\r\n<h2>Construction Waste Crusher</h2>\r\nThis is the processing plant where the waste from a recycle crusher is processed and  recycled leading to the accumulation of waste to be reduced and a lot of  construction materials to be generated through recycling.\r\nThere are two aspects to a construction waste crusher, the stationary  crusher and the mobile crusher. In a stationary crusher the recycle  crushers are to be deposited to a certain site. On the other mobile  crusher, as the name says is mobile and can arrive at the point where  recycling of crusher has to take place in the form of two wheeled  transport platform. It is flexible to the needs of the companies.\r\n<h3>Recycle Crusher of Construction Waste</h3>\r\nIn the concrete recycling process the concrete needs to be crushed in  order to turn into a crusher so as to make the procedure for recycling  easier, hence the name recycle crusher.\r\n\r\nThere are several types of rock crushers that are used for this purpose:\r\n•    <strong>Jaw Crusher</strong> is the type of recycle crusher used for the crushing of  large sized materials and ores which require a crushing pressure of  less than 320 Mpa. It is efficient in its work by crushing down  something huge into various tiny pieces. It can popularly be used mainly  for the mining or sand making equipment. But it has other uses too  apart from these.\r\n•    <strong>Impact Crusher</strong> is a type of recycle crusher has specifically been  made to deal with materials that have a side length of around 500mm and  require pressure strength of less than 350 Mpa. Its useful mainly in the  area of expressway building, hydro power stations and in stone  crushing. There are two kinds of impact crusher, first one is the common  impact crusher and the second one is a hammer impact crusher.\r\n•    <strong>Mobile Concrete Crusher</strong> this is the most advanced form of crusher  which has been built on the basis of a very new technology. It has  mobile features as well as the adaptability to working site features.  This type of recycle crusher too comes in two styles, Hydraulic Driven track  mobile plant and Crawler type mobile crushers.','Recycle Crusher','','inherit','open','open','','66-revision-6','','','2011-06-27 17:15:16','2011-06-27 17:15:16','',66,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/66-revision-6',0,'revision','',0),(275,1,'2011-06-27 17:14:16','2011-06-27 17:14:16','What is a Recycle Crusher? When renovations take place or when structures which have been made  of concrete are entirely demolished, they create rubble which needs to  be recycled. Concrete or crusher recycling is the name given to the  recycling of rubble created by such demolition. Before this  method of recycling was available, concrete waste was deposited as landfills but the  advantages of concrete crusher recycling has made it a better option especially  since now various environmental laws have been set up against dumping of  waste. Crusher recycling also keeps the costs of construction low.\r\n<h1>By-product of a Recycle Crusher</h1>\r\nRecycling of concrete leads to the production of industrial by-products  which include fly ash, slag and silica fume. Apart from these by-products, waste  materials are a raw material for several other products including cement and  tires etc. Cement makes use of silica, calcium, alumina and iron which  are the recycled by-product of sand from steel casting and fly ash from  power stations. Kiln waste is dust that is produced in the production of  cement and despite it being a dust; it is still recycled back as a raw  material into kiln. Even concrete which has become very old has a use;  it can be used as a granular fill for road beds after