ent.com/blog/59-revision',0,'revision','',0),(190,1,'2011-06-06 21:21:43','2011-06-06 21:21:43','<strong></strong><strong>Portable concrete plants</strong> allow builders to produce concrete for the project at the construction site itself instead of having to order it at a fixed concrete plant site and then transport it at a heavy cost. Instead of being loaded at a distant site, the raw materials, along with water are discharged to the mixer truck on the construction site. Portable concrete plants, like normal concrete batch plants, use the same batch systems and equipment produce concrete. The concrete developed in concrete batch plants as well as portable concrete batch plants are used for foundations, paving material for roads, parking lots, tilt-up walls, poured in place, precast and prestressed.\n<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-139\" title=\"portable-concrete-plants\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/portable-concrete-plants.jpg\" alt=\"portable concrete plants\" width=\"330\" height=\"269\" />Portable Concrete Plants</h1>\nThe main purpose of portable concrete plants has been to provide  affordable and single unit with highway affordability, while keeping a  low profile and a minimum amount of set-up time. These portable plants  have reduced many a headache for construction site managers because they  are very efficient in production and at the same time easy to use and  handle. The main purpose of a portable concrete batch plant is to reduce  time and expenses.\n<h2>Portable Concrete Plants - general nature</h2>\nPortable concrete plants have been developed to ease the complete  process of mixing and manufacturing cement. The portable concrete plants  are self erecting structures and can be constantly moved and  transported throughout the construction site according to the  requirements of the contractor. The entire structuring and components of portable concrete batch plants must be sturdy enough to  handle the continuous transportation from one place to another. If the  plant is unable to handle the rigorous processes at the construction  site for long, the contractors will have to hire someone else for the  job or even revert to concrete produced at the factories. This could  lead to inefficiency and higher costs and defeats the purpose of using a  portable concrete plant. In addition to this, they are compact,  powerful and extremely useful for various job sites. When built with  care and properly assembled, the portable concrete batch plant performs  at its best and exceeds customers’ expectations.\n<h3>Range of Portable Concrete Plants</h3>\nThere is a whole range of portable concrete plants available to fit the  budget constraints of different customers. Starting from the design and  specification stages to the manufacturing and installation and  commissioning of a portable concrete plant, all top manufacturers take  the necessary steps to make sure the final product is up to the mark and  does not cause any problems for the client.\n\nPortable concrete plants can also be customized as per requirements of  clients and customers. Full account of available space and existing  equipments is taken into consideration in order to deliver dynamic  solutions. Another important aspect is that if the requirement is not  long term, the portable concrete batch plants or concrete batch plants  can be rented as well.\n\nAlong with installation of portable concrete batch plants, their  security is also very crucial. Gate operators are available to solve  that problem. Gate operators of varied designs and specification are  available to suit the utility of people. Be it electronic, battery  operated, folding, luxury, remote controlled or others, gate operators  are capable of making your residence, office, industrial area,  commercial space or any other area absolutely secure.\n\nFor more detailed information and brands contact <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/products-portable-concrete-batch-plants.php#apachesqp\">portable concrete plants</a>','Portable Concrete Plants','','inherit','open','open','','53-revision-13','','','2011-06-06 21:21:43','2011-06-06 21:21:43','',53,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/53-revision-13',0,'revision','',0),(62,1,'2011-05-24 17:34:34','2011-05-24 17:34:34','<strong>Ready mix plants</strong>, also referred to as a batching plant, for concrete allows builders to manufacture customized cement  and transport that mixture to the  construction site as and when required. The product is normally  transported from the ready mix plants using truck mounted  transit mixers. This enables customized concrete to be produced which is  required on the construction sites. The world’s first ready mix  concrete plant was set up in 1930s, but the actual boom in the industry  began in 1960s, and has never looked back since.\n<h1>Ready Mix Plants</h1>\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-110\" title=\"ready-mix-plant\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/ready-mix-plant.jpg\" alt=\"ready mix plants\" width=\"300\" height=\"160\" />\nThe main purpose of concrete <em>ready mix plants</em> is to provide  concrete to construction sites on a timely basis. When a batch of ready mix concrete  is required, the nearest plants are normally favored in order to  minimize transport time and cost. At the plant, raw materials are stored  in hoppers and silos and mixed using advanced computerized systems. The  ready mixed concrete plant is required to equip itself with up-to-date  equipments, such as transit mixer, concrete pump, and concrete batching  plant, which needs visualized production management software and also  PLC controller. Experienced batchers continuously monitor the processes  to ensure that the quality of cement meets the expectations of the client.\n\n<strong>HOW DO READY MIX PLANTS WORK WITH MATERIALS?</strong>\n•    Hydration: After raw materials, water, and cement are combined, the  mixture remains in a fluid state for about 5 hours, allowing  transportation, placements and finishing at the intended building site.  During hydration, cement crystals radiate and mesh with crystals of  water and other raw materials, resulting in stiffening and hardening of  cement. Once the cement is thoroughly mixed, it should be placed at the  required places before it sets.\n\n•    Proportioning: This involves proportioning of a <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: black;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concrete\">concrete</a> mix  design to make it economical and enable it to achieve the properties  required for its intended use. The experts at the ready mixed concrete  plant can select the material proportions for the performance you  require, or you may specify your requirements yourself through job  specifications.\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">READY MIX PLANTS</span></h2>\n<strong>Types</strong>\n\nThere are four different types of ready mix concrete.\n•    <strong>Truck Mixed Concrete:</strong> In this method, all the raw ingredients are  mixed during the transit. Most of the water is batched at the plant and  the mixer drum is turned at fast speeds during loading of the materials.  The mixing can be done either at the job site, in the plant itself  before dispatch, or during the transit period itself.\n\n•   <strong> Shrink Mixed Concrete:</strong> This method involves initial mixing in  the plant mixer after which the concrete is loaded into the truck mixer  to be mixed completely during the transit. The amount and time of mixing  done in the truck mixer is determined using mixer uniformity tests.\n\n•   <strong> Central Mixed Concrete:</strong> The entire mixing process is completed in  the plant mixer and the cement is loaded onto the truck mixer for  transport. In this method, the truck mixer is used mainly as a  transporter of the ready mix concrete.\n<h3>Ready Mix Plants</h3>\nUsing ready mix concrete at your construction site could be an excellent  decision which would result in higher efficiency and time savings along  with reduced costs. Also, every load of concrete you use will be fresh  as it has been mixed either on the way to the construction site or at  the construction site itself. Moreover, large construction assignments  such as road paving can depend on a consistent quality of cement in  every truckload. Another aspect where costs are reduced is that labor  at the construction site earlier used for cement production can be  assigned other jobs, and there is also reduced requirement for storage  space at the site.\n\n<strong>Related Articles:</strong>\n\n<address>For more information on purchasing <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com\" target=\"_blank\">concrete batch plants </a>\n</address> <address>More information on <a title=\"portable concrete plants\" href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/portable-concrete-plants\">portable concrete plants</a></address> <address>More information on <a href=\"http://http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/mobile-batch-plant\">mobile match plant</a></address> <address> </address> <address>More information on <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com\">ready mix plants</a></address> <address> </address> <address> </address>','Ready Mix Plants','','publish','open','open','','ready-mix-plants','','','2011-06-21 16:50:48','2011-06-21 16:50:48','',0,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/?p=62',0,'post','',0),(63,1,'2011-05-16 21:37:12','2011-05-16 21:37:12','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision','','','2011-05-16 21:37:12','2011-05-16 21:37:12','',62,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/62-revision',0,'revision','',0),(64,1,'2011-05-16 21:37:32','2011-05-16 21:37:32','Ready mix concrete allows builders to manufacture customized cement  in a factory or batching plant and transport that mixture to the  construction site as and when required. The p