concrete.\r\n•    Truck Mixed Concrete: In this method, all the raw ingredients are  mixed during the transit. Most of the water is batched at the plant and  the mixer drum is turned at fast speeds during loading of the materials.  The mixing can be done either at the job site, in the plant itself  before dispatch, or during the transit period itself.\r\n\r\n•    Shrink Mixed Concrete: This method involves initial mixing in  the plant mixer after which the concrete is loaded into the truck mixer  to be mixed completely during the transit. The amount and time of mixing  done in the truck mixer is determined using mixer uniformity tests\r\n•    Central Mixed Concrete: The entire mixing process is completed in  the plant mixer and the cement is loaded onto the truck mixer for  transport. In this method, the truck mixer is used mainly as a  transporter of the ready mix concrete.\r\nUsing ready mix concrete at your construction site could be an excellent  decision which would result in higher efficiency and time savings along  with reduced costs. Also, every load of concrete you use will be fresh  as it has been mixed either on the way to the construction site or at  the construction site itself. Moreover, large construction assignments  such as road paving can depend on a consistent quality of cement in  every truckload. Another aspect where costs are reduced is that labour  at the construction site earlier used for cement production can be  assigned other jobs, and there is also reduced requirement for storage  space at the site.','Ready Mix Plants','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-2','','','2011-05-16 21:37:32','2011-05-16 21:37:32','',62,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/62-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(267,1,'2011-06-06 21:59:03','2011-06-06 21:59:03','RCC MIXERS\r\nRCC which is short for Roller Compacted Concrete is a blend of concrete  which is similar to the usual concrete but just has a different ratio of  ingredients used in it. The ingredi