a headache for construction site managers because they are very efficient in production and at the same time easy to use and handle. The main purpose of a portable concrete batch plant is to reduce time and expenses.  By removing the travel time required from a stationary concrete batch plant over long distances to a job site, a portable concrete batch plant allows producers the flexibility to complete projects in remote locations, move the batch plant to another site quickly upon project completion, and permitting issues are greatly reduced or eliminated.\r\n<h2>Portable Concrete Plants - general nature</h2>\r\nPortable <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: black;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concrete\">concrete</a> plants have been developed to ease the complete process of mixing and manufacturing ready mix concrete. Most portable concrete plants are self erecting and can be constantly moved and transported throughout the construction site or site to site according to the requirements of the contractor. The entire structure and components of portable concrete batch plant must be sturdy enough to handle the continuous transportation from one place to another. When built with the proper engineering, the portable concrete batch plant performs at its best and exceeds customers’ expectations.\r\n<h3>Range of Portable Concrete Plants</h3>\r\nThere is a whole range of portable concrete plants available to fit the budget constraints of different customers. Starting from the design and specification stages to the manufacturing and installation and commissioning of a portable concrete plant, all top manufacturers take the necessary steps to make sure the final product is up to the mark and does not cause any problems for the client.\r\n\r\nPortable concrete plants can also be customized as per requirements of clients and customers. Full account of available space and existing equipments is taken into consideration in order to deliver dynamic solutions. Another important aspect is that if the requirement is not long term, the portable concrete batch plant or concrete batch plants can be rented as well.\r\n\r\nWhen purchasing a portable concrete batch plant, factors to consider include:  overall travel height, whether or not the batch plant is truly \"self-erecting\" or will require the use of a crane, and yards per hour of productivity that will be required to complete a project.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Related Articles:</strong>\r\n\r\n<address><a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com\">Concrete Batch Plants</a></address> <address>Mobile Batch Plants</address> <address>Ready Mix Plants</address> <address>Batch Plant Mixers\r\n</address>For more detailed information and brands contact <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/products-portable-concrete-batch-plants.php#apachesqp\">portable concrete plants</a>','Portable Concrete Plants','','inherit','open','open','','53-revision-22','','','2011-06-08 19:59:01','2011-06-08 19:59:01','',53,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/53-revision-22',0,'revision','',0),(249,1,'2011-06-18 20:14:31','2011-06-18 20:14:31','Gulf Atlantic Equipment\n\nCall: (800) 792-7427\n\n[contact_form]','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','247-autosave','','','2011-06-18 20:14:31','2011-06-18 20:14:31','',247,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/247-autosave',0,'revision','',0),(247,1,'2011-06-18 20:08:05','2011-06-18 20:08:05','Gulf Atlantic Equipment\r\n\r\nCall: (800) 792-7427\r\n\r\n[contact_form]','Contact Us','','publish','open','open','','contact-us','','','2011-06-18 20:13:27','2011-06-18 20:13:27','',0,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/?page_id=247',0,'page','',0),(248,1,'2011-06-18 20:07:53','2011-06-18 20:07:53','','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','247-revision','','','2011-06-18 20:07:53','2011-06-18 20:07:53','',247,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/247-revision',0,'revision','',0),(85,1,'2011-05-16 17:38:56','2011-05-16 17:38:56','[caption id=\"attachment_7\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"294\" caption=\"Comanche Products Concrete Batch Plant\"]<a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Comanche-Products-concrete-batch-plant.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-7\" title=\"Comanche-Products-concrete-batch-plant\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Comanche-Products-concrete-batch-plant.jpg\" alt=\"concrete batch plant\" width=\"294\" height=\"259\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nCONCRETE BATCH PLANTS\r\nA concrete batch plant is the place where concrete is mixed with different types of ingredients like sand, water, rock, silver, etc. Generally there are two types of concrete plants used for mixing concrete. The first one is Ready Mix plant and second is Central Mix batch plant. In ready mix plants, all ingredients are mixed with each other except water. Water is added to it when it is used for construction at the construction site. On the other hand, central mix batch plant includes all ingredients with water and is used when construction is going to be started.\r\n\r\nThe center of any concrete batching plant is the mixer. There are three types of mixers: tilt, pan, and twin shaft mixer. The twin shaft mixer ensures even mixture of concrete and large output, whereas the tilt mixer offers a consistent mix with much less maintenance, labor and cost.\r\nConcrete batch plants are mostly used by construction companies where they produce a large amount of concrete. They are quite expensive and a company cannot afford more than one plant. If a company is going to increase its concrete batch plant then they have to increase their labor, transportation cost and many more costs.\r\n\r\nTYPES OF CONCRETE BATCH PLANTS Concrete batch plants fall into two broad categories. One is a permanent high capacity batching plant which is normally constituted of silos, bins, concrete batchers, conveyors, and control equipments. Listed below are three types of permanent high capacity batching plants.\r\n\r\n•    Robo-mix plants: This is the most popular form of concrete batch plants and consists of a drum mixer. It is the most ideal to use it on construction site.\r\n•    Hydro-mix plants: This is the second most popular type of concrete batch plant and consists of a conveyor belt discharge system. It is used with conventional truck mixers.\r\n•    Bin-Fed Batching Plant: This plant is fully automatic and has its own hydraulic off-loading legs.\r\n\r\nThe other type of concrete batching plants which are rapidly gaining popularity and can be seen widely used in construction sites, is called the Mobile (or Portable) batching plant. The mobile batching units include the structure which carries the batchers, conveyors, scales, control equipment and small silos to be used at the construction site. They provide a lot of cost and time savings and increase efficiency at the building site. Many a construction headache has been solved using this relatively cheaper alternative. facility which allows construction site managers to reduce cost but maintain quality.\r\n\r\nWith the advent of technology, most modern concrete batch plants use computer aided control to assist in the quick and accurate measurement of ingredients, as well as coordinate the functioning of various parts and accessories for safe operation. Since the quality and performance of concrete is highly dependent on the water content, these sophisticated systems will use moisture probes to gauge the amount of water that is part of the aggregate (sand and rock) material during weighing.  If there is a need for changing the water content, it will automatically do so.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Concrete Batch Plants','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-5','','','2011-05-16 17:38:56','2011-05-16 17:38:56','',2,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/2-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(97,1,'2011-05-18 16:59:53','2011-05-18 16:59:53','[caption id=\