phisticated systems will use moisture probes to gauge the amount of water that is part of the aggregate (sand and rock) material during weighing.  If there is a need for changing the water content, it will automatically do so.\r\n\r\nRelated Articles:\r\n\r\n<address>link back to main site</address><address>link to a post #1</address><address>link to a post #2\r\n</address>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Concrete Batch Plants','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-22','','','2011-05-18 19:40:14','2011-05-18 19:40:14','',2,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/2-revision-22',0,'revision','',0),(105,1,'2011-05-16 21:30:11','2011-05-16 21:30:11','<a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/FHA1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-15\" title=\"FHA\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/FHA1.jpg\" alt=\"FHA logo\" width=\"100\" height=\"97\" /></a>The Federal Highway Administration will hold three online informational meetings next week about plans for Interstate 3.\r\n\r\nThe FHA is working on a \"Conceptual Feasibility Report\" to identify potential alignments that connect designated urban areas, develop cost estimates for various design levels, and recommend implementation steps. Interstate 3 may someday run from Savannah to Knoxville, Tenn.\r\n\r\nHearings are for noon and 6:30 p.m. Tuesday, May 17, 2011 and 10 a.m. next Wednesday, May 18, 2011.\r\n\r\nTo participate in the noon Tuesday meeting, register online at: <a title=\"FHA Tuesday @ noon\" href=\"The Federal Highway Administration will hold three online informational meetings next week about plans for Interstate 3.  The FHA is working on a &quot;Conceptual Feasibility Report&quot; to identify potential alignments that connect designated urban areas, develop cost estimates for various design levels, and recommend implementation steps. Interstate 3 may someday run from Savannah to Knoxville, Tenn.  Hearings are for noon and 6:30 p.m. Tuesday, May 17, 2011 and 10 a.m. next Wednesday, May 18, 2011.  To participate in the noon Tuesday meeting, register online at https://www3.gotomeeting.com/register/739903006; the 6:30 p.m. Tuesday meeting at https://www3.gotomeeting.com/register/868736998 and the Wednesday morning meeting at https://www3.gotomeeting.com/register/128482726.\" target=\"_blank\">https://www3.gotomeeting.com/register/739903006</a>; the 6:30 p.m.\r\nTuesday meeting at: <a title=\"FHA Tuesday @ 6:30 pm\" href=\"https://www3.gotomeeting.com/register/868736998 \" target=\"_blank\">https://www3.gotomeeting.com/register/868736998 </a>\r\nand the Wednesday morning meeting at <a title=\"FHA Wednesday morning\" href=\"https://www3.gotomeeting.com/register/128482726\" target=\"_blank\">https://www3.gotomeeting.com/register/128482726</a>.\r\n\r\nCredit source: <a title=\"Online Athens\" href=\"http://www.onlineathens.com/stories/051111/new_827232932.shtml\" target=\"_blank\">OnlineAthens.com</a>','FHA plans meetings for I-3 proposal','','inherit','open','open','','3-revision-10','','','2011-05-16 21:30:11','2011-05-16 21:30:11','',3,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/3-revision-10',0,'revision','',0),(106,1,'2011-05-16 21:38:06','2011-05-16 21:38:06','Ready mix concrete allows builders to manufacture customized cement  in a factory or batching plant and transport that mixture to the  construction site as and when required. The product is normally  transported from the ready mix concrete plants using truck mounted  transit mixers. This enables customized concrete to be produced which is  required on the construction sites. The world’s first ready mix  concrete plant was set up in 1930s, but the actual boom in the industry  began in 1960s, and has never looked back since.\r\nThe main purpose of ready mix concrete plants is to provide concrete to  construction sites on a timely basis. When a batch of ready mix concrete  is required, the nearest plants are normally favoured in order to  minimize transport time and cost. At the plant, raw materials are stored  in hoppers and silos and mixed using advanced computerized systems. The  ready mixed concrete plant is required to equip itself with up-to-date  equipments, such as transit mixer, concrete pump, and concrete batching  plant, which needs visualized production management software and also  PLC controller. Experienced batchers continuously monitor the processes  to ensure that the quality of cement meets the expectations of the  client.\r\nHOW IT’S MADE?\r\n•    Hydration: After raw materials, water, and cement are combined, the  mixture remains in a fluid state for about 5 hours, allowing  transportation, placements and finishing at the intended building site.  During hydration, cement crystals radiate and mesh with crystals of  water and other raw materials, resulting in stiffening and hardening of  cement. Once the cement is thoroughly mixed, it should be placed at the  required places before it sets.\r\n\r\n•    Proportioning: This involves proportioning of a concrete mix  design to make it economical and enable it to achieve the properties  required for its intended use. The experts at the ready mixed concrete  plant can select the material proportions for the performance you  require, or you may specify your requirements yourself through job  specifications.\r\nTYPES OF READY MIX CONCRETE\r\nThere are four different types of ready mix concrete.\r\n•    Truck Mixed Concrete: In this method, all the raw ingredients are  mixed during the transit. Most of the water is batched at the plant and  the mixer drum is turned at fast speeds during loading of the materials.  The mixing can be done either at the job site, in the plant itself  before dispatch, or during the transit period itself.\r\n\r\n•    Shrink Mixed Concrete: This method involves initial mixing in  the plant mixer after which the concrete is loaded into the truck mixer  to be mixed completely during the transit. The amount and time of mixing  done in the truck mixer is determined using mixer uniformity tests\r\n•    Central Mixed Concrete: The entire mixing process is completed in  the plant mixer and the cement is loaded onto the truck mixer for  transport. In this method, the truck mixer is used mainly as a  transporter of the ready mix concrete.\r\nUsing ready mix concrete at your construction site could be an excellent  decision which would result in higher efficiency and time savings along  with reduced costs. Also, every load of concrete you use will be fresh  as it has been mixed either on the way to the construction site or at  the construction site itself. Moreover, large construction assignments  such as road paving can depend on a consistent quality of cement in  every truckload. Another aspect where costs are reduced is that labour  at the construction site earlier used for cement production can be  assigned other jobs, and there is also reduced requirement for storage  space at the site.','Ready Mix Plants','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-3','','','2011-05-16 21:38:06','2011-05-16 21:38:06','',62,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/62-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(107,1,'2011-05-18 22:00:17','2011-05-18 22:00:17','Ready mix concrete allows builders to manufacture customized cement  in a factory or batching plant and transport that mixture to the  construction site as and when required. The product is normally  transported from the ready mix concrete plants using truck mounted  transit mixers. This enables customized concrete to be produced which is  required on the construction sites. The world’s first ready mix  concrete plant was set up in 1930s, but the actual boom in the industry  began in 1960s, and has never looked back since.\n\nThe main purpose of ready mix concrete plants is to provide concrete to  construction sites on a timely basis. When a batch of ready mix concrete  is required, the nearest plants are normally favoured in order to  minimize trans