0),(137,1,'2011-05-23 16:38:47','2011-05-23 16:38:47','<strong>Ready mix plants</strong>, also referred to as a batching plant, for concrete allows builders to manufacture customized cement  and transport that mixture to the  construction site as and when required. The product is normally  transported from the ready mix plants using truck mounted  transit mixers. This enables customized concrete to be produced which is  required on the construction sites. The world’s first ready mix  concrete plant was set up in 1930s, but the actual boom in the industry  began in 1960s, and has never looked back since.\n<h1>Ready Mix Plants</h1>\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-110\" title=\"ready-mix-plant\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/ready-mix-plant.jpg\" alt=\"ready mix plants\" width=\"300\" height=\"160\" />\nThe main purpose of concrete <em>ready mix plants</em> is to provide  concrete to construction sites on a timely basis. When a batch of ready mix concrete  is required, the nearest plants are normally favored in order to  minimize transport time and cost. At the plant, raw materials are stored  in hoppers and silos and mixed using advanced computerized systems. The  ready mixed concrete plant is required to equip itself with up-to-date  equipments, such as transit mixer, concrete pump, and concrete batching  plant, which needs visualized production management software and also  PLC controller. Experienced batchers continuously monitor the processes  to ensure that the quality of cement meets the expectations of the client.\n\n<strong>HOW IT’S MADE?</strong>\n•    Hydration: After raw materials, water, and cement are combined, the  mixture remains in a fluid state for about 5 hours, allowing  transportation, placements and finishing at the intended building site.  During hydration, cement crystals radiate and mesh with crystals of  water and other raw materials, resulting in stiffening and hardening of  cement. Once the cement is thoroughly mixed, it should be placed at the  required places before it sets.\n\n•    Proportioning: This involves proportioning of a <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: black;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concrete\">concrete</a> mix  design to make it economical and enable it to achieve the properties  required for its intended use. The experts at the ready mixed concrete  plant can select the material proportions for the performance you  require, or you may specify your requirements yourself through job  specifications.\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">READY MIX PLANTS</span></h2>\n<strong>Types</strong>\n\nThere are four different types of ready mix concrete.\n•    <strong>Truck Mixed Concrete:</strong> In this method, all the raw ingredients are  mixed during the transit. Most of the water is batched at the plant and  the mixer drum is turned at fast speeds during loading of the materials.  The mixing can be done either at the job site, in the plant itself  before dispatch, or during the transit period itself.\n\n•   <strong> Shrink Mixed Concrete:</strong> This method involves initial mixing in  the plant mixer after which the concrete is loaded into the truck mixer  to be mixed completely during the transit. The amount and time of mixing  done in the truck mixer is determined using mixer uniformity tests.\n\n•   <strong> Central Mixed Concrete:</strong> The entire mixing process is completed in  the plant mixer and the cement is loaded onto the truck mixer for  transport. In this method, the truck mixer is used mainly as a  transporter of the ready mix concrete.\n<h3>Ready Mix Plants</h3>\nUsing ready mix concrete at your construction site could be an excellent  decision which would result in higher efficiency and time savings along  with reduced costs. Also, every load of concrete you use will be fresh  as it has been mixed either on the way to the construction site or at  the construction site itself. Moreover, large construction assignments  such as road paving can depend on a consistent quality of cement in  every truckload. Another aspect where costs are reduced is that labor  at the construction site earlier used for cement production can be  assigned other jobs, and there is also reduced requirement for storage  space at the site.\n\n<strong>Related Articles:</strong>\n\n<address>For more information on purchasing <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com\" target=\"_blank\">concrete batch plants </a>\n</address> <address>More information on <a title=\"portable concrete plants\" href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/portable-concrete-plants\">portable concrete plants</a></address> <address>More information on <a href=\"http://http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/mobile-batch-plant\">mobile match plant</a></address> <address> </address> <address>More information on <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com\">ready mix plants</a>\n</address>&nbsp;\n<div id=\"suggestions\">\n<ul>\n	<li>Your keyword density is too low, you need more repetitions on your keyword.</li>\n	<li>You need a H2 tag with your keyword inside it.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','Ready Mix Plants','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-26','','','2011-05-23 16:38:47','2011-05-23 16:38:47','',62,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/62-revision-26',0,'revision','',0),(139,1,'2011-05-23 16:44:30','2011-05-23 16:44:30','','portable-concrete-plants','','inherit','open','open','','portable-concrete-plants-2','','','2011-05-23 16:44:30','2011-05-23 16:44:30','',53,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/portable-concrete-plants.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(140,1,'2011-05-23 16:42:49','2011-05-23 16:42:49','<strong>Portable concrete plants</strong> allow builders to produce concrete for  the project at the construction site itself instead of having to order  it at a fixed concrete plant and then transport it at a heavy cost.  Instead of being mixed