crete producers have to continuously think of innovative solutions to cater to the requirements of clients. Any small difference in the quality of material supplied or any delays in transportation could be very costly for both client and producer. However, with the advent of mobile batching plants, there has been a great increase in the quality of concrete supplied and delivery times have also been reduced significantly.<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-148\" title=\"mobile-batch-plants\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/mobile-batch-plants.jpg\" alt=\"mobile batch plants\" width=\"320\" height=\"150\" />\n<h2>What are mobile batch plants?</h2>\nUnlike conventional mixer trucks, mobile batching plants carry the necessary materials with them to the construction site. This includes all forms of aggregates, water, cement, and other components which may be added according to the requirements of the job. Earlier, engineers made use of mobile placing booms as well as truck-mounted concrete pumps. Apart from this they had no other option to get concrete on site. The most commonly used method was using plants in the city for mixing and then transporting the concrete onto the construction site via mixer trucks.\nAdvantage of mobile However, since concrete is sensitive to time and heat, spending too much time on the road results in a significant fall in quality. According to one of the pioneers in the industry, concrete coming out of the chute of volumetric mixer is always fresh unlike that of a conventional mixer truck. In addition to this, there is great savings on wastage as only that amount of concrete is produced which is required at the construction site.\nSand and aggregate are carried in open topped bins with a rigid proportioning belt at the bottom. Blending is achieved by calibrated and adjustable strike off gates at the rear of the bins. Cement sufficient for full load of materials is contained behind the aggregates in a top loading, weather-tight bin with inspection windows, and metered through sequential auger vane feeders directly into the mixer throat. Water and admixtures are injected into the enclosed mixer throat at its bottom where the dry materials enter. The blended concrete is then discharged into a chute at  eye level.\nThe entire production process is monitored just like at a normal concrete batching plant. All production is monitored through the analogue metering system which is connected to the main drive shaft allowing the operator to gauge exactly how much concrete has been made. All you have to do is “pull the lever” until the necessary amount of concrete has been filled. Mobile batching plants are renowned for their low maintenance and operational costs. They are reliable due to the high level of technology involved in producing them and provide accurate results. Mobile batching plants can work in a wide range of environmental conditions and give their maximum potential.\nAnother benefit of mobile batching plants is that they can be quickly adjusted according to the requirements of the job. Since the batching is done at the construction site itself, the adjustments can be done swiftly in a matter of seconds by just adding to the aggregate mix.\nOverall, mobile batching plants have been a welcome addition to the line of batching plants available as they have low operational costs and can be quickly adjusted according to construction site requirements.','Mobile Batch Plants','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-3','','','2011-05-23 17:22:30','2011-05-23 17:22:30','',5,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/5-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(150,1,'2011-05-23 17:23:17','2011-05-23 17:23:17','<h1>MOBILE BATCH  PLANTS</h1>\r\nWith a burgeoning demand for concrete due to increase in construction, concrete producers have to continuously think of innovative solutions to cater to the requirements of clients. Any small difference in the quality of material su