ed concrete plant and then transport it at a heavy cost.  Instead of being mixed in the factory, the raw materials, along with  water are poured directly into the concrete truck mixer in one go.  Portable concrete plants, like normal concrete batch plants, use huge  amounts of sand, gravel, cement and water in order to produce concrete.  The concrete developed in concrete batch plants as well as portable  concrete batch plant is used for foundations, paving material for roads  and parking lots and pipes used for drainage and plumbing.\n<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-139\" title=\"portable-concrete-plants\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/portable-concrete-plants.jpg\" alt=\"portable concrete plants\" width=\"330\" height=\"269\" />Portable Concrete Plants</h1>\nThe main purpose of portable concrete plants has been to provide  affordable and single unit with highway affordability, while keeping a  low profile and a minimum amount of set-up time. These portable plants  have reduced many a headache for construction site managers because they  are very efficient in production and at the same time easy to use and  handle. The main purpose of a portable concrete batch plant is to reduce  time and expenses.\n<h2>Portable Concrete Plants - general nature</h2>\nPortable concrete plants have been developed to ease the complete  process of mixing and manufacturing cement. The portable concrete plants  are self erecting structures and can be constantly moved and  transported throughout the construction site according to the  requirements of the contractor. The entire structuring and components of portable concrete batch plants must be sturdy enough to  handle the continuous transportation from one place to another. If the  plant is unable to handle the rigorous processes at the construction  site for long, the contractors will have to hire someone else for the  job or even revert to concrete produced at the factories. This could  lead to inefficiency and higher costs and defeats the purpose of using a  portable concrete plant. In addition to this, they are compact,  powerful and extremely useful for various job sites. When built with  care and properly assembled, the portable concrete batch plant performs  at its best and exceeds customers’ expectations.\n<h3>Range of Portable Concrete Plants</h3>\nThere is a whole range of portable concrete plants available to fit the  budget constraints of different customers. Starting from the design and  specification stages to the manufacturing and installation and  commissioning of a portable concrete plant, all top manufacturers take  the necessary steps to make sure the final product is up to the mark and  does not cause any problems for the client.\n\nPortable concrete plants can also be customized as per requirements of  clients and customers. Full account of available space and existing  equipments is taken into consideration in order to deliver dynamic  solutions. Another important aspect is that if the requirement is not  long term, the portable concrete batch plants or concrete batch plants  can be rented as well.\n\nAlong with installation of portable concrete batch plants, their  security is also very crucial. Gate operators are available to solve  that problem. Gate operators of varied designs and specification are  available to suit the utility of people. Be it electronic, battery  operated, folding, luxury, remote controlled or others, gate operators  are capable of making your residence, office, industrial area,  commercial space or any other area absolutely secure.\n<div id=\"suggestions\"></div>\nFor more detailed information and brands contact <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/products-portable-concrete-batch-plants.php#apachesqp\">portable concrete plants</a>','Portable Concrete Plants','','inherit','open','open','','53-revision-11','','','2011-05-23 16:57:04','2011-05-23 16:57:04','',53,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/53-revision-11',0,'revision','',0),(158,1,'2011-05-19 02:23:51','2011-05-19 02:23:51','[caption id=\"attachment_7\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"121\" caption=\"Comanche Products Concrete Batch Plant\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-7 \" title=\"Comanche-Products-concrete-batch-plant\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Comanche-Products-concrete-batch-plant.jpg\" alt=\"concrete batch plants\" width=\"121\" height=\"106\" />[/caption]\r\n<h1>CONCRETE BATCH PLANTS</h1>\r\nA <strong>concrete batch plant</strong> is the place where concrete is mixed with different types of ingredients like sand, water, rock, silver, etc. Generally there are two types of concrete plants used for mixing concrete. The first one is Ready Mix plant and second is Central Mix batch plant. In ready mix plants, all ingredients are mixed with each other except water. Water is added to it when it is used for construction at the construction site. On the other hand, central mix batch plant includes all ingredients with water and is used when construction is going to be started.\r\n\r\nThe center of any <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: black;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concrete_batching_plant\">concrete batching plant</a> is the mixer. There are three types of mixers: tilt, pan, and twin shaft mixer. The twin shaft mixer ensures even mixture of concrete and large output, whereas the tilt mixer offers a consistent mix with much less maintenance, labor and cost.\r\n\r\nConcrete batch plants are mostly used by construction companies where they produce a large amount of concrete. They are quite expensive and a company cannot afford more than one plant. If a company is going to increase its concrete batch plant then they have to increase their labor, transportation cost and many more costs.\r\n<h2>TYPES OF CONCRETE BATCH PLANTS</h2>\r\nConcrete batch plants fall into two broad categories. One is a permanent high capacity batching plant which is normally constituted of silos, bins, concrete batchers, conveyors, and control equipments. Listed below are three types of permanent high capacity batching plants.\r\n\r\n•    Robo-mix plants: This is the most popular form of concrete batch plants and consists of a drum mixer. It is the most ideal to use it on construction site.\r\n\r\n•    Hydro-mix plants: This is the second most popular type of concrete batch plant and consists of a conveyor belt discharge system. It is used with conventional truck mixers.\r\n\r\n•    Bin-Fed Batching Plant: This plant is fully automatic and has its own hydraulic off-loading legs.\r\n<h3>Trends in Concrete Batch Plants</h3>\r\nThe other type of concrete batching plants which are rapidly gaining popularity and can be seen widely used in construction sites, is called the Mobile (or Portable) batching plant. The mobile batching units include the structure which carries the batchers, conveyors, scales, control equipment and small silos to be used at the construction site. They provide a lot of cost and time savings and increase efficiency at the building site. Many a construction headache has been solved using this relatively cheaper alternative. facility which allows construction site managers to reduce cost but maintain quality.\r\n\r\nWith the advent of technology, most modern concrete batch plants use computer aided control to assist in the quick and accurate measurement of ingredients, as well as coordinate the functioning of various parts and accessories for safe operation. Since the quality and performance of concrete is highly dependent on the water content, these sophisticated systems will use moisture probes to gauge the amount of water that is part of the aggregate (sand and rock) material during weighing.  If there is a need for changing the water content, it will automatically do so.\r\n\r\nRelated Articles:\r\n\r\n<address>For more information on purchasing <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.