 seconds by just adding to the aggregate mix.\r\n\r\nOverall, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">mobile batching plants</span> have been a welcome addition to the line of batching plants available as they have low operational costs and can be quickly adjusted according to construction site requirements.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/products-portable-concrete-batch-plants.php\r\n<div id=\"suggestions\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your keyword density is too low, you need more repetitions on your keyword.</li>\r\n	<li>You need a H1 tag with your keyword inside it.</li>\r\n	<li>You should point a link to your other pages with keyword as anchor text.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>','Mobile Batch Plants','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-9','','','2011-05-23 17:35:30','2011-05-23 17:35:30','',5,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/5-revision-9',0,'revision','',0),(161,1,'2011-05-23 17:34:52','2011-05-23 17:34:52','<strong>Ready mix plants</strong>, also referred to as a batching plant, for concrete allows builders to manufacture customized cement  and transport that mixture to the  construction site as and when required. The product is normally  transported from the ready mix plants using truck mounted  transit mixers. This enables customized concrete to be produced which is  required on the construction sites. The world’s first ready mix  concrete plant was set up in 1930s, but the actual boom in the industry  began in 1960s, and has never looked back since.\r\n<h1>Ready Mix Plants</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-110\" title=\"ready-mix-plant\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/ready-mix-plant.jpg\" alt=\"ready mix plants\" width=\"300\" height=\"160\" />\r\nThe main purpose of concrete <em>ready mix plants</em> is to provide  concrete to construction sites on a timely basis. When a batch of ready mix concrete  is required, the nearest plants are normally favored in order to  minimize transport time and cost. At the plant, raw materials are stored  in hoppers and silos and mixed using advanced computerized systems. The  ready mixed concrete plant is required to equip itself with up-to-date  equipments, such as transit mixer, concrete pump, and concrete batching  plant, which needs visualized production management software and also  PLC controller. Experienced batchers continuously monitor the processes  to ensure that the quality of cement meets the expectations of the client.\r\n\r\n<strong>HOW IT’S MADE?</strong>\r\n•    Hydration: After raw materials, water, and cement are combined, the  mixture remains in a fluid state for about 5 hours, allowing  transportation, placements and finishing at the intended building site.  During hydration, cement crystals radiate and mesh with crystals of  water and other raw materials, resulting in stiffening and hardening of  cement. Once the cement is thoroughly mixed, it should be placed at the  required places before it sets.\r\n\r\n•    Proportioning: This involves proportioning of a <a style=\"text-decoration: none; color: black;\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concrete\">concrete</a> mix  design to make it economical and enable it to achieve the properties  required for its intended use. The experts at the ready mixed concrete  plant can select the material proportions for the performance you  require, or you may specify your requirements yourself through job  specifications.\r\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">READY MIX PLANTS</span></h2>\r\n<strong>Types</strong>\r\n\r\nThere are four different types of ready mix concrete.\r\n•    <strong>Truck Mixed Concrete:</strong> In this method, all the raw ingredients are  mixed during the transit. Most of the water is batched at the plant and  the mixer drum is turned at fast speeds during loading of the materials.  The mixing can be done either at the job site, in the plant itself  before dispatch, or during the transit period itself.\r\n\r\n•   <strong> Shrink Mixed Concrete:</strong> This method involves initial mixing in  the plant mixer after which the concrete is loaded into the truck mixer  to be mixed completely during the transit. The amount and time of mixing  done in the truck mixer is determined using mixer uniformity tests.\r\n\r\n•   <strong> Central Mixed Concrete:</strong> The entire mixing process is completed in  the plant mixer and the cement is loaded onto the truck mixer for  transport. In this method, the truck mixer is used mainly as a  transporter of the ready mix concrete.\r\n<h3>Ready Mix Plants</h3>\r\nUsing ready mix concrete at your construction site could be an excellent  decision which would result in higher efficiency and time savings along  with reduced costs. Also, every load of concrete you use will be fresh  as it has been mixed either on the way to the construction site or at  the construction site itself. Moreover, large construction assignments  such as road paving can depend on a consistent quality of cement in  every truckload. Another aspect where costs are reduced is that labor  at the construction site earlier used for cement production can be  assigned other jobs, and there is also reduced requirement for storage  space at the site.\r\n\r\n<strong>Related Articles:</strong>\r\n\r\n<address>For more information on purchasing <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com\" target=\"_blank\">concrete batch plants </a>\r\n</address> <address>More information on <a title=\"portable concrete plants\" href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/portable-concrete-plants\">portable concrete plants</a></address> <address>More information on <a href=\"http://http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/mobile-batch-plant\">mobile match plant</a></address> <address> </address> <address>More information on <a href=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com\">ready mix plants</a>\r\n</address>','Ready Mix Plants','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-28','','','2011-05-23 17:34:52','2011-05-23 17:34:52','',62,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/62-revision-28',0,'revision','',0),(242,1,'2011-06-13 23:03:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Concrete Crushing and Recycling: Problems and Solutions</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>Concrete Recycling is a growth industry.  If you are considering entering this market or are having problems in your current operation, there are solutions available to make your operation more successful and profitable.\r\n\r\nSo, what are the major issues that give concrete crushing and recycling contractors heartburn?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Rebar and wire mesh makes pre-breaking concrete slabs a miserable job, but it is necessary to get slabs down to size to fit into the crusher.</li>\r\n	<li>Operational costs associated with replacement parts, particularly the wear parts like hammers (blowbars) and curtain liners can be costly and affect productivity.</li>\r\n	<li>Operational costs associated with the general maintenance of the equipment, and downtime due to rebar entanglement and/or breakdowns.</li>\r\n	<li>Obtaining necessary permits for site and/or equipment within a reasonable time following award of a contract for on-site crushing.</li>\r\n	<li>Control of dust and noise during operations in areas where authorities are less than accommodating and agencies often conflict.</li>\r\n	<li>Complexities within the equipment design that force owners to deal with unnecessary downtime and ill-trained factory support.</li>\r\n	<li>Lack of replacement parts when time is of essence ... nothing off-the-shelf ... all metric and foreign sourced.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFortunately, Gulf Atlantic Industrial Equipment, your Universal Engineering dealer, has equipment to provide the solutions to these problems and the dealer and factory application knowledge to avoid the pitfalls of concrete recycling. Universal Engineering products are designed and manufactured in the USA and are available as both stationary and portable crushing units.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The VersaCap Primary Concrete Recycle Impact Crusher\r\n</span></strong>The VersaCap Recycle Impactor is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">the most versatile impact crusher on the market</span> with interchangeable components to \"custom fit\" your specific application.  Combined with the versatility factor, the heavy-duty construction ensures unmatched durability maintaining its capital value while it minimizes downtime and increases profitability.  In addition to those features common to most recycling impactors, the VersaCap also allows for a number of features that enable it to function cost-effectively in the recycling of highly friable materials.\r\n\r\nIn recycling applications, the VersaCap will convert large slabby feed into 1-1/2” minus at 200tph, 300 tph, and 400 tph depending on the model size. The cast monoblock primary curtain is reversible, but also features replaceable wear edges to add longer life to this massive casting.  If so desired, the monoblock may be replaced by a fully-lined primary curtain weldment.\r\n\r\nThe fully-lined second curtain is known for its unmatched “forgiveness” with almost twice the retraction capability for hydraulic relief over competitive models. The VersaCap is also available with a selection of rotor assemblies designed for a wide variety of applications. The typical “3-Bar” and “4-Bar” arrangements are both available, and can accomodate medium or heavy hammers (blowbars). These reversible hammers feature a protruding leading edge that provides for greater through-put capacity over the wear life of the hammer.\r\n\r\nThe robust housing of the VersaCap accepts a variety of feed chute arrangements for every application, and an optional third curtain (apron) may be added in the field to enhance the wide range of output gradations. Perhaps the most unique feature of the VersaCap is the “Adjust-on-the-fly” capability available as an option.  Adjusting the VersaCap curtains may be done with a simple hydraulic-shim arrangement, or with the optional hydraulic operating system. The hydraulic operating system can be further enhanced with PLC controls for the ultimate in system integration. This remarkable recycle impact crusher, is a culmination of technologies developed, tested and field-proven over the past 25 years by Universal Engineering Corp.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The RCP Impactor Recycle Crusher for Concrete and Asphalt\r\n</span></strong>The RCP Impactors have been specifically designed to meet the need of the growing market for recycled concrete and asphalt materials. These Universal impactors feature an extra-wide feed opening to accommodate large slabby material more efficiently. Commonly used in single concrete crusher systems, the massive primary impact chamber allows optimum expansion of the material in process and superior flow consistency. The primary curtain is available with interchangeable liners made in a variety of alloys, or with a solid cast manganese MonoBlock. The secondary curtain has interchangeable liners, also available in a variety of alloys, field-proven for their extended wear life when processing heavily reinforced concrete. The heart of the RCP Impactor is the heavy duty large diameter rotor. This massive one-piece weldment consists of discs that are made from high yield strength steel, and precision-cut back up bars with replaceable face plates. This field-proven rotor incorporates a keyless shaft and is designed to handle rebar and wire mesh cleanly and efficiently. This impactor is available with a 4-bar rotor to allow for maximum range of rotor tip speed, or a 3-bar rotor which is particularly well suited for a variety of recycle applications.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The H-Series Jaw Recycle Crusher\r\n</span></strong><strong>H-Series Jaw Crushers </strong>offer “Adjust-On-The-Fly” capability with an integral system of hydraulic cylinders. This system provides for hydraulic relief and automatic reset as the uncrushable passes the discharge point. The H-Series jaw offers finger-tip control over adjustment of the discharge setting while under load.\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Base Frame </strong>- Rigid one-piece fabricated base frame\r\n\r\n<strong>Massive Steel Pitman </strong>- Heavily reinforced to provide the ability to absorb massive shock loads and superior compressive force over the entire crushing chamber.\r\n\r\n<strong>Large Balanced Flywheels </strong>- Supply continuous driving force to the crushing action.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reversible Manganese Jaw Plates - </strong>Provide for a severe duty wear surface that work hardens and allows for maximum wear life. The Model 3264 Recycle Jaw includes replaceable toes to support both the stationary and movable jaw plates. On the 3264 the jaw plates are identical and interchangeable.\r\n\r\n<strong>Replaceable Cheek Plates </strong>- Prevent wear on the sides of the crusher base. The three piece design as shown here is typical of the Model 3264 Recycle Jaw. Helps minimize replacement cost and downtime for maintenance.\r\n\r\n<strong>Massive Steel Pitman </strong>- Heavily reinforced to provide the ability to absorb massive shock loads and superior compressive force over the entire crushing chamber.\r\n\r\n<strong>Large Balanced Flywheels </strong>- Supply continuous driving force to the crushing action.\r\n\r\n<strong>Adjust-On-The-Fly Hydraulic System </strong>- Features a bank of industry-standard cylinders and provides for hydraulic relief with auto-reset, hydraulic clearing, and adjustments of the discharge setting at the touch of a finger while under full load. Provides safety relief for uncrushable material and a means to optimize production for greater profits.\r\n\r\n<strong>Toggle Plate </strong>- Allows for continous movement between the hydraulic assembly and the pitman. The location of the toggle plate at the lowest point on the pitman provides more crushing action at the toe and more “pull through”. Steep toggle angle and large eccentric offset provide more crushing throughout the chamber.\r\n\r\n<strong>Hydraulic Cylinders </strong>- Provide the force necessary to hold and maintain the jaw setting and allow hydraulic clearing. Each cylinder is individually plumbed for ease of maintenance. The auto reset function is activated by a limit switch and assures immediate return to the hydraulic setting automatically following any tramp iron event.\r\n\r\nFor optimal performance, ease of portability, reliable spare parts supply, and the most durablility and versatility in the concrete crushing equipment market today, contact Gulf Atlantic Industrial Equipment at 800-792-7427.','Concrete Crushers','','draft','open','open','','concrete-recycling-plants','','','2011-06-13 23:03:00','2011-06-13 23:03:00','',0,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/?p=242',0,'post','',0),(274,1,'2011-06-27 17:13:58','2011-06-27 17:13:58','What is a Recycle Crusher? When renovations take place or when structures which have been made  of concrete are entirely demolished, they create rubble which needs to  be recycled. Concrete or crusher recycling is the name given to the  recycling of rubble created by such demolition. Before this  method of recycling was available, concrete waste was deposited as landfills but the  advantages of concrete crusher recycling has made it a better option especially  since now various environmental laws have been set up against dumping of  waste. Crusher recycling also keeps the costs of construction low.\n<h1>By-product of a Recycle Crusher</h1>\nRecycling of concrete leads to the production of industrial by-products  which include fly ash, slag and silica fume. Apart from these by-products, waste  materials are a raw material for several other products including cement and  tires etc. Cement makes use of silica, calcium, alumina and iron which  are the recycled by-product of sand from steel casting and fly ash from  power stations. Kiln waste is dust that is produced in the production of  cement and despite it being a dust; it is still recycled back as a raw  material into kiln. Even concrete which has become very old has a use;  it can be used as a granular fill for road beds after being recycled.\n<h2>\nConstruction Waste Crusher</h2>\nThis is the processing plant where the waste from a recycle crusher is processed and  recycled leading to the accumulation of waste to be reduced and a lot of  construction materials to be generated through recycling.\nThere are two aspects to a construction waste crusher, the stationary  crusher and the mobile crusher. In a stationary crusher the recycle  crushers are to be deposited to a certain site. On the other mobile  crusher, as the name says is mobile and can arrive at the point where  recycling of crusher has to take place in the form of two wheeled  transport platform. It is flexible to the needs of the companies.\n<h3>\nRecycle Crusher of Construction Waste</h3>\nIn the concrete recycling process the concrete needs to be crushed in  order to turn into a crusher so as to make the procedure for recycling  easier, hence the name recycle crusher.\n\nThere are several types of rock crushers that are used for this purpose:\n•    <strong>Jaw Crusher</strong> is the type of recycle crusher used for the crushing of  large sized materials and ores which require a crushing pressure of  less than 320 Mpa. It is efficient in its work by crushing down  something huge into various tiny pieces. It can popularly be used mainly  for the mining or sand making equipment. But it has other uses too  apart from these.\n•    <strong>Impact Crusher</strong> is a type of recycle crusher has specifically been  made to deal with materials that have a side length of around 500mm and  require pressure strength of less than 350 Mpa. Its useful mainly in the  area of expressway building, hydro power stations and in stone  crushing. There are two kinds of impact crusher, first one is the common  impact crusher and the second one is a hammer impact crusher.\n•    <strong>Mobile Concrete Crusher</strong> this is the most advanced form of crusher  which has been built on the basis of a very new technology. It has  mobile features as well as the adaptability to working site features.  This type of recycle crusher too has two kinds, Hydraulic Driven track  mobile plant and Crawler type mobile crushers.','Recycle Crusher','','inherit','open','open','','66-revision-4','','','2011-06-27 17:13:58','2011-06-27 17:13:58','',66,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/66-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(167,1,'2011-06-06 21:45:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;\">The GreyStone Dewatering Screen is available in three different models—the <strong>DS-488</strong> (4-ft x 8-ft),<strong> DS-6010 </strong>(5-ft x 10-ft) and <strong>DS-7212 </strong>(6-ft  x 12-ft)—to efficiently dewater up to 300 TPH with no runoff or water  pools. While most concrete and masonry sands typically retain from 18 to  24 percent moisture, the GreyStone Dewatering Screen cuts that moisture  down to as low as 10 percent—providing salable material in less than a  day. It utilizes two vibrators that initiate a linear motion, driving  particles in an uphill, downhill or horizontal direction. A  high-frequency liquid/solids separator allows producers to easily adjust  bed depth, table tilt and vibrator variables to remove up to 50 percent  of the water, no matter how wet the material is. The urethane deck  dewaters a broad range of particle sizes and can preserve fines smaller  than 200 mesh.</span>\r\n\r\nThe Aggre-Dry® Fine Material Washer Screen  combines a fine material screw and  dewatering screen to produce sand and gravel products with a moisture  content as low as 8 to 13 percent, by weight, while using only 30 hp to  wash and dewater up to 100 TPH.\r\nHere’s how the energy- and  cost-efficient Aggre-Dry FMW Screen washes and dewaters aggregate  material: a standard GreyStone inclined single-spiral fine material  washer (FMW) initially dewaters the material, doing the bulk of the  work. At the same time, the rotation of the dewatering screw scrubs the  material to help remove surface dirt. The action of the screw flights  sends the sand up the inclined tub, and ensures that the dewatering  screen located at the top of the flights will be evenly fed. The  vibratory dewatering screen further removes moisture from the sand. This  combined process produces a caked, dry sand product that neither an  inclined dewatering screw nor a vibratory screen can separately achieve.\r\nThe  GreyStone dewatering screen, curved around the spiral flights on the  Aggre-Dry FMW Screen, has several unique features. A 0.25-mm screen  opening reduces the amount of material that can fall through the screen.  The feed from the screw allows the material to build to a bed depth of  14 inches on the screen, squeezing additional moisture from the sand as  the vibratory motors move it along the length of the screen cloth,  further reducing moisture content.\r\nIn its most innovative feature,  this GreyStone unit re-introduces the throughs from the screen back into  the screw’s washing process, where the screw portion of the unit again  pushes it to the unit’s dewatering screen, increasing the amount of  salable product. This process eliminates the need for costly pumps and  cyclone sand separation systems — along with the additional horsepower  this equipment requires. In fact, the Aggre-Dry FMW Screen should use  less than half of the horsepower required to process the same tonnage of  spec product on a traditional screen / cyclone system. In addition,  GreyStone has increased the water handling capacity of these units,  making the Aggre-Dry even more versatile for aggregate producers.\r\nAs  production of these units increases, GreyStone will offer them in all of  the company’s standard fine material washer sizes, from 36-inches x  28-feet to 84-inches x 38 feet.\r\nGreyStone manufactures a complete  line of field-proven portable and semi-portable washing/screening  plants, sand classification tanks and systems, single and twin fine  material dewatering screws, single and twin coarse material washers, log  washers, advanced computer control systems, portable sand plants, water  clarifiers, rotary and vibrating screens, portable conveyors and radial  stackers, blade mills, dewatering screens, portable screening plants,  twin jets, cutter heads and aggregate reclaiming systems.\r\n\r\n<strong>D</strong>ewatering screens allow producers to sell  material faster by eliminating waiting periods for stockpile drying.  Many concrete and masonry sands typically retain from 18 to 24 percent  moisture, which generally requires between one-to-two weeks of drying  time before it can be sold. At the end of your operation,  Dewatering Screens can receive a high percentage of water-saturated fine  material and produce a dense, compact cake that rides up the belt and  forms a pile with no runoff or water pools. The end result is a dry,  transportable product—with a moisture content as low as 8 percent—that  can be sold in less than a day.\r\n\r\nA number of models are available to handle a variety of  capacities to efficiently dewater up to 350  tons per hour. GreyStone’s Dewatering Screens are constructed of  high-quality ASTM A36 structural steel for years of trouble-free service  life.\r\n\r\n<strong>Features and Benefits of Dewatering Screens</strong>\r\n• Adapts to each plant’s unique material by combining the adjustable motor force in conjunction with the adjustable bed tilt. Once setup is achieved with favorable steady-state conditions, operation starts with a simple flip of a switch.\r\n• The sand stockpile produced stacks high and nearly dry, without forming water pools at the base of the equipment. Eliminating water runoff from material stockpiles helps producers answer local environmental concerns.\r\n• A high-frequency separator allows producers to easily adjust bed depth, table tilt and vibrator variables to remove up to 50 percent of the water, while maintaining maximum production no matter how wet the material is.\r\nTwo vibrators initiate a linear motion, driving particles in an uphill, downhill or horizontal direction—so water is strained down through the sand bed and below the screen deck.\r\n• A urethane deck with a 1/4-mm aperture allows the user to dewater a broad range of particle sizes. The deck can handle up to 14 inches of material depth, making use of the bottom thin layer of material as a secondary “screen,” allowing the deck to preserve fines smaller than 200 mesh.\r\n• A +/- 5-degree bed angle tilt allows producer to better adapt to material volume, gradation and water retention changes and create the proper material bed depth.\r\n\r\nWith high quality classifier configurations and the right equipment to  supply all your washing, classifying and dewatering equipment needs,  Gulf Atlantic Industrial Equipment, Inc. can custom-design a complete operation to meet your specific  application and production requirements. You can send them a sample of  your pit run material for a free sieve analysis and recommendation.','Greystone Dewatering Screen','','draft','open','open','','','','','2011-06-06 21:45:11','2011-06-06 21:45:11','',0,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/?p=167',0,'post','',0),(168,1,'2011-05-25 15:08:59','2011-05-25 15:08:59','','Greystone Dewatering Screen','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision','','','2011-05-25 15:08:59','2011-05-25 15:08:59','',167,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/167-revision',0,'revision','',0),(169,1,'2011-05-25 15:09:23','2011-05-25 15:09:23','<object width=\"480\" height=\"390\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube-nocookie.com/v/lCVRAde35BQ?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube-nocookie.com/v/lCVRAde35BQ?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"480\" height=\"390\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed></object>','Greystone Dewatering Screen','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-2','','','2011-05-25 15:09:23','2011-05-25 15:09:23','',167,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/167-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(170,1,'2011-05-25 15:09:46','2011-05-25 15:09:46','<object width=\"480\" height=\"390\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube-nocookie.com/v/lCVRAde35BQ?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube-nocookie.com/v/lCVRAde35BQ?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US&amp;rel=0\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"480\" height=\"390\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed></object>','Greystone Dewatering Screen','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-3','','','2011-05-25 15:09:46','2011-05-25 15:09:46','',167,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/167-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(173,1,'2011-06-01 14:54:29','2011-06-01 14:54:29','[caption id=\"attachment_7\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"121\" caption=\"Comanche Products Concrete Batch Plant\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-7 \" title=\"Comanche-Products-concrete-batch-plant\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/Comanche-Products-concrete-batch-plant.jpg\" alt=\"concrete batch plants\" width=\"121\" height=\"106\" />[/caption]\r\n<h1>CONCRETE BATCH PLANTS</h1>\r\n<p>A concrete batch plant is a manufacturing facility where concrete is mixed with different types of ingredients. To make concrete mix water, cement, stone and sand! The formula seems simple, but the reality of concrete manufacturing is far more complex. The development of formulas for concrete requires advanced scientific skills. The quality of the cement and aggregates, the dosage and the proportions are just some of the variables that influence the properties of concrete.</p>\r\n<p>Generally there are several types of concrete plants used for mixing concrete.  Stationary Concrete Batch Plants are located in a permanent location and secured with concrete tie down structures.  Portable Concrete Batch Plants generally have wheeled units available to enable the transport of the silos and main plant structure from one site to another with minimal disassembly required.<br /><br />\r\nA Mobile Concrete Batch Plant is the most easily moveable type of ready mixed concrete plant.  The Mobile plant is typically supported on a single axle chassis that can be attached to a semi and transported rapidly from site to site.  All of the above plants can be adapted with a central drum mixer to enable wet mix concrete production for projects such as dams and bridges, etc. </p>\r\n<p>The center of any central mix concrete batching plant is the mixer. There are three main types of mixers available on a ready mix plant: tilt, pan, and twin shaft mixers.  Depending on the application required, concrete batch plant operations can be designed to produce ready mixed concrete, concrete blocks, architectural concrete products, precast concrete, pre-stressed concrete, structural bridge members, and even concrete light poles.  Most concrete batch plants store different stones, sand and cements for the types of concrete that each plant is capable of producing. They create unique mixes to deliver customized performance suitable for each construction need. Through extensive research, Ready Mix Producers utilize innovative mix designs to produce performance concretes. </p>\r\n<h2>Trends in Concrete Batch Plants</h2>\r\n<p>The other type of concrete batching plant which is rapidly gaining popularity and can be seen widely used in construction sites, is called the <strong>Mobile (or Portable) Batching Plant</strong>. The mobile batching units include the structure which carries the batchers, conveyors, scales, control equipment and small silos to be used at the construction site. They provide a lot of cost and time savings and increase efficiency at the building site. <br /><br />\r\nWith the advent of technology, most modern concrete batch plants use computer aided control to assist in the quick and accurate measurement of ingredients, as well as to coordinate the functioning of various parts and accessories for safe operation. Since the quality and performance of concrete is highly dependent on the water content, these sophisticated systems will use moisture probes to gauge the amount of water that is part of the aggregate (sand and rock) material during weighing.  If there is a need for changing the water content, it can be programmed to automatically do so.</p>\r\n<p>Concrete is the most used manmade material in the world, with nearly three tons used annually for each man, woman and child. Concrete has been around for centuries and is an integral part of every civilization. The ancient Romans first used primitive mixes of sand, gravel, lime and gypsum to create enduring concrete structures, such as the Pantheon, that are still standing today.<br /><br />\r\nConcrete technology in the modern age has dramatically improved. Ready Mix Producers manufacture concrete in state-of-the-art plants that utilize sophisticated computers to accurately batch the correct proportions of ingredients to create a consistent, high-quality product.</p>\r\n','Concrete Batch Plants','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-26','','','2011-06-01 14:54:29','2011-06-01 14:54:29','',2,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/2-revision-26',0,'revision','',0),(174,1,'2011-06-01 15:01:13','2011-06-01 15:01:13','[capti