ent. Initially, before this  method of recycling, concrete waste was deposited as landfills but the  advantages of crusher recycling has made it a better option especially  since now various environmental laws have been set up against dumping of  waste. Crusher recycling also keeps the costs of construction low.\nRecycling of concrete leads to the production of industrial by products  which include fly ash, slag and silica fume. Apart from this, waste  materials are a raw material for several products including cement and  tires etc. Cement makes use of silica, calcium, alumina and iron which  are the recycled by product of sand from steel casting and fly ash from  power stations. Kiln waste is dust that is produced in the production of  cement and despite it being a dust; it is still recycled back as a raw  material into kiln. Even concrete which has become very old has a use;  it can be used as a granular fill for road beds after being recycled.\nConstruction Waste Crusher\nThis is the processing plant where waste crusher is processed and  recycled leading to the accumulation of waste to be reduced and a lot of  construction materials to be generated through recycling.\nThere are two parts to a construction waste crusher, the stationary  crusher and the mobile crusher. In a stationary crusher the recycle  crushers are to be deposited to a certain site. On the other mobile  crusher, as the name says is mobile and can arrive at the point where  recycling of crusher has to take place in the form of two wheeled  transport platform. It is flexible to the needs of the companies.\nConstruction Waste Crusher for the Recycle\nIn the concrete recycling process the concrete needs to be crushed in  order to turn into a crusher so as to make the procedure for recycling  easier, hence the name recycle crusher. There are several types of stone  crushers that are used for this purpose:\n•    Jaw Crusher is the type of recycle crusher used for the crushing of  large sized materials and ores which require a crushing pressure of  less than 320 Mpa. It is efficient in its work by crushing down  something huge into various tiny pieces. It can popularly be used mainly  for the mining or sand making equipment. But it has other uses too  apart from these.\n•    Impact Crusher This type of recycle crusher has specifically been  made to deal with materials that have a side length of around 500mm and  require pressure strength of less than 350 Mpa. Its useful mainly in the  area of expressway building, hydro power stations and in stone  crushing. There are two kinds of impact crusher, first one is the common  impact crusher and the second one is a hammer impact crusher.\n•    Mobile Concrete Crusher this is the most advanced form of crusher  which has been built on the basis of a very new technology. It has  mobile features as well as the adaptability to working site features.  This type of recycle crusher too has two kinds, Hydraulic Driven track  mobile plant and Crawler type mobile crushers.','Recycled Crusher','','inherit','open','open','','66-revision-2','','','2011-06-03 19:54:41','2011-06-03 19:54:41','',66,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/66-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(200,1,'2011-06-06 17:18:24','2011-06-06 17:18:24','<h1>MOBILE BATCH  PLANTS</h1>\nWith the introduction of mobile batch plants as a response to burgeoning demand for concrete due to increase in construction, concrete producers continuously response with innovative solutions to cater to the requirements of clients. Any small difference in the quality of material supplied or any delays in transportation could be very costly for both client and producer. However, with the advent of <strong>mobile batch plants</strong> or mobile batching plants, there has been a great increase in the quality of concrete supplied and delivery times have also been reduced significantly.<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-148\" title=\"mobile-batch-plants\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/mobile-batch-plants.jpg\" alt=\"mobile batch plants\" width=\"320\" height=\"150\" />\n<h2>What are mobile batch plants?</h2>\nUnlike conventional mixer trucks, mobile batching plants carry the necessary materials with them to the construction site. This includes all forms of aggregates, water, cement, and other components which may be added according to the requirements of the job. Earlier, engineers made use of mobile placing booms as well as truck-mounted concrete pumps. Apart from this they had no other option to get concrete on site. The most commonly used method was using plants in the city for mixing and then transporting the concrete onto the construction site via mixer trucks.\n<h3>Advantage of mobile batch plants</h3>\nHowever, since concrete is sensitive to time and heat, spending too much time on the road results in a significant fall in quality. According to one of the pioneers in the industry, concrete coming out of the chute of volumetric mixer is always fresh unlike that of a conventional mixer truck. In addition to this, there is great savings on wastage as only that amount of concrete is produced which is required at the construction site.\n\nSand and aggregate are carried in open topped bins with a rigid proportioning belt at the bottom. Blending is achieved by calibrated and adjustable strike off gates at the rear of the bins. Cement sufficient for full load of materials is contained behind the aggregates in a top loading, weather-tight bin with inspection windows, and metered through sequential auger vane feeders directly into the mixer throat. Water and admixtures are injected into the enclosed mixer throat at its bottom where the dry materials enter. The blended concrete is then discharged into a chute at  eye level.\n\nThe entire production process is monitored just like at a normal concrete batching plant. All production is monitored through the analogue metering system which is connected to the main drive shaft allowing the operator to gauge exactly how much concrete has been made. All you have to do is “pull the lever” until the necessary amount of concrete has been filled. <em>Mobile batching plants</em> are renowned for their low maintenance and operational costs. They are reliable due to the high level of technology involved in producing them and provide accurate results. Mobile batching plants can work in a wide range of environmental conditions and give their maximum potential.\n\nAnother benefit of mobile batching plants is that they can be quickly adjusted according to the requirements of the job. Since the batching is done at the construction site itself, the adjustments can be done swiftly in a matter of seconds by just adding to the aggregate mix.\n\nOverall, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">mobile batching plants</span> have been a welcome addition to the line of batching plants available as they have low operational costs and can be quickly adjusted according to construction site requirements.\n\nhttp://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/products-portable-concrete-batch-plants.php\n<div id=\"suggestions\">\n<ul>\n	<li>Your keyword density is too low, you need more repetitions on your keyword.</li>\n	<li>You need a H1 tag with your keyword inside it.</li>\n	<li>You should point a link to your other pages with keyword as anchor text.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','Mobile Batch Plants','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-10','','','2011-06-06 17:18:24','2011-06-06 17:18:24','',5,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/5-revision-10',0,'revision','',0),(202,1,'2011-06-06 22:20:51','2011-06-06 22:20:51','<h1>MOBILE BATCH  PLANTS</h1>\nWith the introduction of mobile batch plants as a response to burgeoning demand for concrete due to an increase in construction, concrete producers continuously responded with innovative solutions to cater to the requirements of clients. Any small difference in the quality of material supplied or any delays