  which has been built on the basis of a very new technology. It has  mobile features as well as the adaptability to working site features.  This type of recycle crusher too comes in two styles, Hydraulic Driven track  mobile plant and Crawler type mobile crushers.\n\n&nbsp;\n<div id=\"suggestions\">\n<ul>\n	<li></li>\n	<li>You definitely want to include an image and set the alt tag to your keyword.</li>\n	<li>You should point a link to your other pages with keyword as anchor text.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','Recycle Crusher','','inherit','open','open','','66-revision-7','','','2011-06-27 19:27:22','2011-06-27 19:27:22','',66,'http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/blog/66-revision-7',0,'revision','',0),(281,1,'2011-06-27 19:27:42','2011-06-27 19:27:42','What is a Recycle Crusher? When renovations take place or when structures which have <img class=\"alignright\" title=\"Recycle Crusher\" src=\"http://www.gulfatlanticequipment.com/product-images/products-crusher10.jpg\" alt=\"recycle crusher\" width=\"145\" height=\"148\" />been made  of concrete are entirely demolished, they create rubble which needs to  be recycled. Concrete or crusher recycling is the name given to the  recycling of rubble created by such demolition. Before this  method of recycling was available, concrete waste was deposited as landfills but the  advantages of concrete crusher recycling has made it a better option especially  since now various environmental laws have been set up against dumping of  waste. Crusher recycling also keeps the costs of construction low.\r\n<h1>By-product of a Recycle Crusher</h1>\r\nRecycling of concrete leads to the production of industrial by-products  which include fly ash, slag and silica fume. Apart from these by-products, waste  materials are a raw material for several other products including cement and  tires etc. Cement makes use of silica, calcium, alumina and iron which  are the recycled by-product of sand from steel casting and fly ash from  power stations. Kiln w